content:
To test calls in your contact center:

Finish setting up Service Cloud Voice.

REQUIRED USER PERMISSIONS: Contact Center Agent permission set.

Open the Omni-Channel utility, set your availability, and enable your microphone.

After a few seconds, you'll be able to make and receive calls on the Phone tab.

Call your contact center from a separate phone. The incoming call should appear in the Omni-Channel utility.

To answer, click the checkmark button. Verify that the Voice Call record page is automatically completed with information about the call.

Make an outbound call by entering a number and clicking "Call" or by using click-to-dial. Verify that the fields on the Voice Call record page are automatically completed with information about the call.
title: Testing Service Cloud Voice
